content: The following IASP Staff are working hard to create this website: Dale Schmidt, Kris Lukkarila, Yaa Cuguano, Elizabeth Endres and Marleda Di Pierri. A huge thank you to all of them plus the back office support of Vladimir Reid and Jeff Spring at TSC and initial project manager Grace Stahre at Fuse IQ.

tag: html body text center table tbody tr td table tbody tr td span
content: We are the largest multidisciplinary international association in the field of pain. Founded in 1973, the International Association for the Study of Pain® (IASP) is a non-profit professional organization dedicated to furthering research on pain and improving the care of patients with pain.

tag: html body text center table tbody tr td table tbody tr td span
content: Membership in IASP is open to scientists, physicians, dentists, psychologists, nurses, physical therapists, and other health professionals actively engaged in pain research and to those who have special interest in the diagnosis and treatment of pain. Currently IASP has more than 6,900 members from 106 countries.
